    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>To Treat Women With Respect</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Hugh Prestwood letter on Brent Staples's June 26 column on Central Park attacks holds television and movies have normalized, validated and glorified crude sexuality, vulgarity and boorish behavior, not violence against women</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Brent Staples writes (Editorial Observer, June 26) that the attacks against women by '' 'ordinary' young men'' in Central Park show ''the extent to which harassment and violence against women have been normalized'' in our society. What has truly been normalized, validated and glorified in our society, through television and movies, is crude sexuality, vulgarity and boorish behavior.</p>
        <p>HUGH PRESTWOOD  Greenport, N.Y., June 27, 2000</p>
      </block>
